FBIS4-38089 "drnes124_p_94011" FBIS-NES-94-124 Daily Report 28 Jun 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Government Seen Making Progress Against Militia Government Seen Making Progress Against Militia Four Groups Call For Cease-Fire NC2806063494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 0330 GMT 28 Jun 94 NC2806063494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Persian BFN [Text] Four Afghan jihadi groups have called for an immediate and unconditional cease-fire among all the conflicting factions in Afghanistan. The Central News Unit reports from Islamabad that following their meeting in Islamabad, Mojaddedi, leader of the National Salvation Party; Mohammadi, leader of the Islamic Revolution Movement; Mohseni, leader of the Islamic Movement; and Gilani, leader of the National Movement, called for the Leadership Council to convene to examine Afghanistan's future rule. Afghan President Rabbani's presidential term expires today.
